Create/Upload Content

Create

The new option in the main menu allow a new system object to be created. Each system object can be created in the the context of a Project, Folder,Task, Cultural object, Document etc.

To create a new system object:

  1. Select Create / Upload from main menu
  2. Select the context where the new object to be created
  3. Select the type of the object to be created from the dropdown menu
  4. Fill the additional data needed for creating the object
  5. Choose a Template from the dropdown menu
  6. Click the Create button

Upload

ConservationSapace allows you to upload different media content - documents, image files, audio files, video files. The new content can be uploaded in the context of any other system object.

To upload the file:

  1. Select the Create / Upload from main menu and the "Upload" option
  2. Select the context you want the file to be uploaded
  3. Select "Select file.." option and chose the file from you local drive
  4. The type of the content will be automatically recognized ("Document" or "Image", "Audio", "Video")
  5. Fill any other data if the selected content type requires any
  6. Choose a Template from the dropdown menu
  7. Click the Upload button
